Document: ResourceImporterWAV
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimporterwav.rst
Summary: Describes the WAV resource importer in Godot, highlighting its advantages and configuration options.
WAV is an uncompressed format, which can provide higher quality compared to Ogg Vorbis and MP3. It also has the lowest CPU cost to decode. This means high numbers of WAV sounds can be played at the same time, even on low-end devices. By default, Godot imports WAV files using the lossy Quite OK Audio compression. You may change this by setting the compress/mode property.
---CHUNK---
Document: ResourceImporterWAV
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimporterwav.rst
Summary: This document describes the WAV audio resource importer in Godot Engine.

This document describes the WAV audio resource importer in Godot Engine. It is used to import audio files in WAV format into Godot projects.

Inherits: ResourceImporter < ResourceImporter.

Methods:
Method: get_importer_name() → StringName
    Returns the name of the importer.

Method: get_visible_name() → StringName
    Returns the visible name of the importer.

Method: get_recognized_extensions() → PackedStringArray
    Returns the file extensions that this importer can recognize.

Method: import(source_file: String, save_path: String, options: Dictionary, platform_variants: Array[String], gen_files: Array[String]) → Error
    Imports the given audio file.

    Parameters:
    source_file (String): The path to the source audio file.
    save_path (String): The path where the imported resource should be saved.
    options (Dictionary): A dictionary of import options.
    platform_variants (Array[String]): An array of platform variants.
    gen_files (Array[String]): An array of generated files.

    Returns:
    Error: An Error code indicating the success or failure of the import process.

Import Options:
    Format (int): The audio format to use. Possible values:
        - WAV_FORMAT_MONO (0): Mono audio.
        - WAV_FORMAT_STEREO (1): Stereo audio.
        - WAV_FORMAT_44_KHZ (0): 44.1 kHz sample rate.
        - WAV_FORMAT_48_KHZ (1): 48 kHz sample rate.
        - WAV_FORMAT_11_KHZ (2): 11 kHz sample rate.
        - WAV_FORMAT_22_KHZ (3): 22 kHz sample rate.
        - WAV_FORMAT_32_BIT (0): 32-bit audio.
        - WAV_FORMAT_16_BIT (1): 16-bit audio.
        - WAV_FORMAT_8_BIT (2): 8-bit audio.

    Note: The import options are combined using bitwise OR. For example, to import a mono, 44.1 kHz, 16-bit audio file, you would use the following options: WAV_FORMAT_MONO | WAV_FORMAT_44_KHZ | WAV_FORMAT_16_BIT.
---CHUNK---
